http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/kerala/Sudheeran-flays-%E2%80%98politics-of-hatred%E2%80%99/article13985685.ece

Kerala Pradesh Congress Committee (KPCC) president V.M. Sudheeran has said that the Sangh Parivar is trying to sow the seeds of politics of hatred in the State.Addressing a public function at Puthiyatheru here on Wednesday during a reception to the Jana Raksha Yatra led by him, Mr. Sudheeran said that the BJP president Amit Shah had forged an alliance with SNDP Yogam general secretary Vellappally Natesan to trade the Sangh Parivar's ‘politics of hatred.’ Mr. Natesan who is leading a movement started by Sree Narayana Guru is now trying to use it for the Sangh Parivar’s campaign, he alleged.Mr. Sudheeran said that the UDF’s liquor policy was now endorsed by the Supreme Court. He called on the CPI(M) to make clear its stand on the government's liquor policy.Congress leaders M.M. Hassan, N. Peethambara Kurup, K. Sudhakaran, Satheeshan Pacheni, T. Siddique, P. Ramakrishnan and Binud Krishna were among those present at the reception. The yatra was accorded a public reception here in the evening.